<div id="outline-container-unnumbered-3" class="outline-2 topic-list-def">
<h2 id="unnumbered-3">Other packages</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-unnumbered-3">
<p>
Some interesting packages that we probably won't cover directly:
</p>

<dl class="org-dl">
<dt><a href="http://biopython.org/wiki/Main_Page">Biopython</a></dt><dd>Wide collection of tools for biology</dd>
<dt><a href="https://bitbucket.org/james_taylor/bx-python/wiki/Home">bx-python</a></dt><dd>Genome analysis tools</dd>
<dt><a href="http://docs.python.org/3.3/library/collections.html">collections</a></dt><dd>Some useful datatypes, especially <code>defaultdict</code> and
<code>namedtuple</code></dd>
<dt><a href="http://docs.python.org/3.3/library/csv.html">csv</a></dt><dd>Reading and writing of delimited files</dd>
<dt><a href="http://docopt.org/">docopt</a></dt><dd>Convenient and fast way to write command line program</dd>
<dt><a href="http://docs.python.org/3.3/library/fileinput.html">fileinput</a></dt><dd>A good solution for handling standard input and multiple
input files</dd>
<dt><a href="http://docs.python.org/3.3/library/itertools.html">itertools</a></dt><dd>Handy functions for working with iterators</dd>
<dt><a href="http://ipython.org/notebook.html">IPython notebook</a></dt><dd>IPython session within a text document</dd>
<dt><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NumPy">NumPy</a></dt><dd>Multi-dimensional arrays (Pandas is built on top of this)</dd>
<dt><a href="http://statsmodels.sourceforge.net/">statsmodels</a></dt><dd>Statistical library</dd>
</dl>
</div>
</div>


